{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"75d61bcf-47a9-4b8a-a877-c30e7c7df443","content":"Since you already have the dump file collected, the next step is **analysis** — which is outside the scope of the dump-collection skill I have available.\n\nHere's how you can analyze it:\n\n### Using `dotnet-dump analyze` (cross-platform)\n```bash\n# Install the tool\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n\n# Open the dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-app.dmp\n```\n\nUseful SOS commands inside the analyzer:\n| Command | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `pe` (`printexception`) | Show the last exception |\n| `threads` | List all managed threads |\n| `clrstack` | Show managed call stack |\n| `dumpheap -stat` | Heap summary (for OOM) |\n| `syncblk` | Check for deadlocks |\n\n### Typical workflow\n```\n> threads          # find the faulting thread\n> setthread <id>   # switch to it\n> pe               # print the exception\n> clrstack         # see the managed stack trace\n```\n\n### Alternatives\n- **WinDbg** (Windows) — load with `.loadby sos clr` or `.loadby sos coreclr`\n- **lldb + SOS** (Linux/macOS) — `plugin load libsosplugin.so`\n- **Visual Studio** — open the `.dmp` directly for a guided experience\n\nWould you like help running `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file, or do you have a specific error you'd like to investigate?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"112c29cf-fa04-4789-a380-c39d8f81a3bd","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application and wants to analyze it to find the root cause of the crash. Let me help them with this.\n\nLooking at the available skills, I see there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description says it's for **collecting** crash dumps, NOT for analyzing them. It explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the `dump-collect` skill is not appropriate here. Let me help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their dump file.\n\nI should provide guidance on how to analyze the dump file using tools like `dotnet-dump analyze`, WinDbg, or lldb depending on their platform.","outputTokens":539,"requestId":"CB03:3B2241:707862:818A5F:6A052B21"},"id":"bbcce801-2a15-45d4-85fc-4de1cd06c0dc","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:53:51.635Z","parentId":"55bf48f9-fc2f-4bc9-b0a9-0210a51024c5"}
